Program: Discovery
Title: Post-Soviet Science - Germany
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxz6
Last Broadcast Date: 06 December 2001
How the reunification of East and West Germany affected scientific research. The collapse of the German political system after the fall of the Berlin Wall meant re-unification, a huge task involving restructuring on both sides. This programme examines how this affected science, and the new direction it took. Show less